channel.title: Why did you choose your username?
channel.description:
well, why did you choose the name you have now? does it describe your personality, what you like, or do you just like how it sounds?
I choose neon impulse because when I hear it I imagine a futuristic city with a multi-colored neon line flashing through it... So, why did you chose yours?

item.title: Why did you choose your username?
item.dc:creator: Neon_Impulse
item.description:
ok, I’m not feeling lazy anymore, here’s my story:

I was originally planning to call myself ‘‘Sumguy29_the_Neon_Impulse’’ but it was too long for most websites, so now I either call myself Sumguy29 or Neon Impulse. (with the exception of youtube, where I called myself Stickman4EVA for some reason) anyway, here’s the story:

Sum refers to my exceptional ability at arithmetic.
guy refers to my gender.
29 was my family’s old address.
neon refers to a take-away shop my uncle owned, and the replacement texture my cousin made the chargers in half-life, which made them seem to glow all different colors, like neon.
impulse refers to when I first played half-life, I had next to no skill and therefore excessively spammed impulses (mainly 101) into the console whenever I saw an enemy.

…caffeine made me right thatXD
sigh I love pepsi:3
